      "author": "HWY1dot0",
      "description": "## Weekly notes overhaul\n\n**Self-contained weekly notes.** Calendar Hub no longer reads weekly-note settings from the legacy Calendar plugin. The weekly note format, folder, and template you configure in Calendar Hub are now actually used (no more silent fallback to `gggg-[W]ww`).\n\n**Fixes**\n- Newly created weekly notes now show on the calendar immediately. Previously, with \"Detect daily notes in all folders\" enabled, a new weekly note only appeared after a reload. Delete/rename now refresh the weekly index too.\n\n**New — weekly notes aggregate like daily notes**\n- Week numbers show a note-count dot, and selecting a week lists every note for that week below the calendar (same panel as days).\n- Notes are matched by a week-format filename or a frontmatter week field, across folders — multiple notes per week.\n- New settings under *Weekly Note Settings*: detect weekly notes in all folders, folders to scan, extra filename formats, and a frontmatter fallback with configurable fields.\n\nInstall/update via Community Plugins, or download `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css` below.",
