      "author": "HWY1dot0",
      "description": "# Multi Note Calendar beta\n\nThis is a public beta fork of Liam Cain's Calendar plugin for Obsidian.\n\nIt is intended for users who keep multiple date-based notes per day across different folders.\n\n## Added in this beta\n\n- Multiple notes per date.\n- A selected-day note list below the calendar.\n- Vault-wide filename matching.\n- Extra filename date formats such as `YYYYMMDD`.\n- Frontmatter date fallback.\n- Folder filters from both settings and the Calendar sidebar.\n- Solid dots represent note count instead of word count.\n\n## Attribution\n\nThis fork is based on the original Calendar plugin by Liam Cain:\n\nhttps://github.com/liamcain/obsidian-calendar-plugin\n\nThe original project is MIT licensed, and the original copyright notice remains in place.\n\n## Upstream status\n\nAn upstream proposal/PR has been opened. This fork is published under a separate name so users who need this workflow can test it without replacing the official Calendar plugin.\n\n## Beta warning\n\nThis fork changes Calendar's date model from one note per date to multiple notes per date. Please test it on a vault you can recover from backup.\n",
      "draft": false,
      "name": "0.1.0-beta.1",
      "prerelease": true,
      "publishedAt": "2026-05-30T08:34:50Z",
